As of the [[2020 United States census]], there were 692 people, 247 households, and 177 families residing in the town.

===2010 census===
Grantsboro had a population of 688 in 2010.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://www.census.gov/popest/cities/tables/SUB-EST2006-04-37.csv | title = Table 4. Annual Estimates of the Population for Incorporated Places in North Carolina: April 1, 2000 to July 1, 2006 | format = [[comma-separated values|CSV]] | work = | publisher = [[United States Census Bureau]], Population Division | date = 2007-06-28 | accessdate = 2008-04-28}}</ref>

